.Dd July 1, 2026
.Dt ANSIBLE_INIT 8
.Os FreeBSD
.Sh NAME
.Nm ansible_init
.Nd Firstboot ansible-pull initialization rc script
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Cm start
.Nm
.Cm stop
.Nm
.Cm status
.Nm
.Cm enabled
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
script provides automated, unattended system configuration during the initial
boot sequence using
.Xr ansible-pull 1 .
It is explicitly designed to run once when a system is deployed via the
.Cm firstboot
keyword mechanism.
.Pp
When executed, the service constructs an
.Xr ansible-pull 1
command line to clone a specified Git repository and execute a local Ansible
playbook, configuring the FreeBSD host automatically.
.Sh RC.CONF VARIABLES
The
.Nm
script reads configuration variables from
.Pa /etc/rc.conf ,
.Pa /etc/rc.conf.local ,
or
.Pa /etc/rc.conf.d/ansible_init .
.Pp
The following variables are available:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Va ansible_init_enable
.Pq Vt bool
Set to "NO" by default. Set it to "YES" to enable the service.
.It Va ansible_init_host
.Pq Vt str
The base URL or hostname hosting the remote Ansible repository.
Default:
.Pa http://localhost .
.It Va ansible_init_repo
.Pq Vt str
The repository name containing the playbook.
Default:
.Pa ansible-conf-init .
.It Va ansible_init_dest
.Pq Vt str
The root destination directory where the repository will be cloned.
Default:
.Pa /root .
.It Va ansible_init_vars
.Pq Vt str
Path to a directory containing files with local variables passed to the Ansible execution.
Default:
.Pa /root/ansible-vars .
.It Va ansible_init_playbook
.Pq Vt str
The entrypoint playbook file inside the repository to execute.
Default:
.Pa pb-init.yml .
.El
.Sh DEPLOYMENT ENVIRONMENT
The service injects a restricted, safe execution environment via
.Va ansible_init_env
To guarantee that commands executed within the Ansible playbooks can resolve path references to both standard base system binaries and packages installed in standard ports prefixes.
.Pp
The following environment variables are strictly passed to the execution shell:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Ev PATH
.Pa /sbin:/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:%%PREFIX%%/sbin:%%PREFIX%%/bin
.It Ev LANG
.Li en_US.UTF-8
.It Ev LC_ALL
.Li en_US.UTF-8
.El
.Sh INTERNALS
The service translates the
.Xr rc.conf 5
variables into a structured command utilizing the following internal layout:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
%%PREFIX%%/bin/ansible-pull -i hosts \e
    -U <ansible_init_host>/<ansible_init_repo> \e
    -d <ansible_init_dest>/<ansible_init_repo> \e
    -e 'ai_vars=<ansible_init_vars>' \e
    -e 'ai_pull_mode=true' \e
    <ansible_init_playbook>
.Ed
.Pp
The
.Fl e
extra variables flags inject
.Va ai_vars
and
.Va ai_pull_mode
into the playbook scope, allowing the playbook tasks to adapt dynamically to the bootstrap process.
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Pa
.It Pa %%PREFIX%%/etc/rc.d/ansible_init
The rc script itself.
.It Pa /etc/rc.conf
Primary configuration file where parameters are defined.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr ansible-pull 1 ,
.Xr rc.conf 5 ,
.Xr rc 8 ,
.Xr rc.subr 8
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
manual page and script first appeared in 2026.
.Sh AUTHORS
.An -nosplit
The
.Nm
script and this manual page were written by
